  <Mission 
  famTitle="The family at Fuglestein"
  famDesc1="We are a family passionate about carrying on the proud legacy at Fuglestein. For us, fruit growing is not just about production, but about a love for the craft, sustainability, and creating unique products of the highest quality."
  famDesc2="Through generations, the orchard has been the heart of our farm. Every single day, we put a lot of hard work and passion into our craft, so that you can enjoy the authentic taste of Ryfylke – whether you are tasting our fresh apple juice or our home-produced cider. Welcome to the farm!"
  famImgAlt="The family at Fuglestein working together"
  histTitle="The history of the farm"
  histDesc1="Fuglestein is sheltered and south-facing, 70 meters above sea level near the Ryfylke fjord. On top of the moraine here, one can find an ancient burial site from the Iron Age, with at least six burial mounds and two standing stones, where both silver rings and wooden knives have been found."
  histDesc2="But the secret behind the lush growth and the unique sweetness in our fruit lies in the ground. Our soil is rich in phyllite, a nutrient-rich, fossilized clay that makes the soil perfect for fruit growing."
  histDesc3="This tradition is old at the farm; the oldest known apple orchard here is documented as far back as 1838. The combination of warm days, cool autumn nights, and nutrient-rich soil is what gives our fruit that very special color and full-bodied taste you find in your glass."
/>
